<Layout title="Financial Advisor Mortgage (RIA Principal) · Registered Investment Advisor S-Corp / Partnership Principal W-2 + K-1, AUM Recurring Revenue, Form ADV, PE Consolidator (Hightower / Mercer / Captrust) &amp; Post-Sale Asset-Depletion Specialist" description="Registered Investment Advisor (RIA) principal mortgage as practice owner distinct from producer-side advisor sales path. RIA practice principals operating SEC-registered RIA firms (over approximately $100-$110M AUM threshold regulated under Investment Advisers Act of 1940) or state-registered RIA firms (under threshold regulated by state securities boards) typically structured as S-corp election (Form 1120-S) for single-principal practices or partnership (Form 1065) for multi-principal practices, with W-2 reasonable compensation $150K-$400K plus K-1 distributions of remaining net practice income. Junior RIA principal at $50M-$150M AUM earning $250K-$500K W-2 + K-1, mid-tier RIA principal at $150M-$500M AUM earning $500K-$1.5M, established RIA principal at $500M-$2B+ AUM earning $1.5M-$5M+ reflecting AUM-based recurring revenue at 0.50-1.25% annual advisory fee producing highly predictable continuing income stream tied to assets under management volume. Substantial RIA practice valuations at 8-12x annual recurring revenue (ARR) or 2-3x revenue methodology in active PE-backed consolidator transaction market. PE-backed RIA consolidator transactions including Hightower Advisors (PE-backed by Thomas H. Lee Partners), Mercer Advisors (PE-backed by Oak Hill Capital then Genstar Capital), Wealth Enhancement Group (PE-backed by Onex Partners), Captrust (PE-backed by GTCR), Beacon Pointe Advisors, Creative Planning (PE-backed by General Atlantic), Mariner Wealth Advisors, and Edelman Financial Engines producing cash plus rollover equity plus multi-year earnout structure with continuing operating role at acquired consolidator. Form ADV documentation Part 1 registration plus Part 2A brochure maintained with SEC or state securities board. Fiduciary standard duty under Investment Advisers Act of 1940. Charles Schwab Advisor Services (largest RIA custodian post-TD Ameritrade), Fidelity Wealth Advisor Solutions, Pershing BNY Mellon, Raymond James, LPL Financial custodial relationships. CFP credential through CFP Board, Series 65 or Series 66 Investment Adviser Representative status through FINRA. Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corporation analysis for RIA principal K-1 with Form 1084 entity-level cash-flow addbacks, B3-3.1-01 variable income for prior wirehouse W-2 history during breakaway period or post-consolidator-sale continuing operating role, B3-3.1-09 for multi-year earnout and rollover equity vesting in PE-backed consolidator entity, and Asset-Depletion Non-QM for post-consolidator-sale RIA principal on liquid practice-exit reserves amortized over 360 months. Conventional Conforming, Conventional Jumbo, Conventional Super-Jumbo, S-Corp Self-Employed, Multi-Source Jumbo (breakaway), Bank Statement Non-QM, Asset-Depletion Non-QM (post-consolidator-sale), and P&L Statement Only Non-QM (rapid-growth) loan program options. DISTINCT from producer-side financial advisor sales path covering wirehouse advisors at Merrill Lynch, Morgan Stanley, UBS, Wells Fargo Advisors with commission plus AUM-fee participation plus insurance product overrides plus W-2 plus RSU under wirehouse W-2 employment. PE consolidation accelerating, RIA practice valuations at multi-year highs, fee compression industry trend, SEC vs state-registered $100M-$110M AUM threshold regulatory bifurcation, CFP standard and fiduciary push, and Florida RIA growth from no-state-income-tax wealth migration patterns industry dynamics." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/financial-advisors/">
